==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈæntiˌpɑɹtɪkəl/}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''antiparticle''' (''plural'' '''antiparticles''')
# {{particles}} A [[subatomic particle]] corresponding to another [[particle]] with the same [[mass]], [[spin]] and [[mean]] [[lifetime]] but with [[charge]], [[parity]], [[strangeness]] and other [[quantum number]]s flipped in sign.

